REQUIREMENTS:

You will need the following to use Annotateit on your own server:

* A *nix variant (Linux will do nicely)
* The Apache webserver (http://www.apache.org)
* The Perl Programming Language (http://perl.com)
* Several Perl Modules available from cpan (http://search.cpan.org)
	* Data::Dumper
	* DBD::mysql
	* DBI
	* Template
	* Config::Simple
	* Date::Calc
	* IO::File
	* CGI
	* MIME::Lite
	* IO::Handle
	* URI
	* Time::HiRes 
	* Benchmark
	* Calendar::Simple
	* Net::DNS
	* LWP::UserAgent
	* HTTP::Request::Common
	* Digest::MD5
	* File::Basename
	* HTML::Parser
	* Class::Accessor
	* Class::Fields
	* HTML::Scrubber
	* HTML::TokeParser::Simple
* GNU unrtf (http://www.gnu.org/software/unrtf/unrtf.html)
* wvWare (http://wvware.sourceforge.net)
* The MySQL database server (http://www.mysql.com)
* The ability to edit your web server configuration file
* The ability to edit text documents on the server.


SUPPORT

There is some support available.  Of course, Buzzmaven Co will provide
everything you need to run your own Annotateit server.  Also, you may
find some help by using the annotateit-users email list:

http://www.buzzmaven.com/mailman/listinfo.cgi/annotateit-users

Please search the archives before posting.

It is possible if you are experiencing a problem, that there is a bug
filed for it already at

http://bugzilla.buzzmaven.com

Please search for a bug before submitting a new bug report.


CONTRIBUTIONS

Contributions in any form are welcome.  Annotateit needs
documentation, perl programmers, graphic designers, HTML gurus (who
can pick up a simple templating language).

If you want to contribute, please join the annotateit-dev email list:

http://www.buzzmaven.com/mailman/listinfo.cgi/annotateit-dev

